Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention-based seq2seq models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of exponential moving average technique, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the generation of questions from a given passage, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.IR is also a likely sub-category.
